{
  "doc_id": "35930",
  "text": "Unfortunately we do not know of a freely available implementation of the safety simple subset of PSL [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] , and therefore cannot run benchmarks against those. With regards to approaches based on the safety simple subset our main contribution is that we impose no syntactic restrictions on the model checked formulas unlike the safety simple subset that is quite restricted in its allowed syntax. In comparison to the explicit automata approach of [CITATION_5] we can state that our symbolic encoding is exponentially more compact and also handles a larger set of properties, not only the LTL subset.",
